text:
(1) Pearl Street, east side, south from Burling Slip, showing the former 7th Ward Bank Building, (No. 234 Pearl Street), at the S.E. corner. This bank was incorporated in 1833 and reorganized in 1865. Effingham Schieffelin was its president about 1840; Jno. W. Lawrence, occupying the same position in 1857. July 1924. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same. Overhead, on pearl Street, runs the South Ferry Division of the Second and Third Aves. Elevated lines. May 1924. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
title: Manhattan: Pearl Street - Burling Slip
